# React Effect Discipline

- Use `useEffect` only to synchronize with external systems (DOM, browser APIs, network, third-party libs, subscriptions).
- If something can be derived from props/state, compute it during render instead of effect-synced state.
- Use `useMemo` only when that render-time computation is measurably expensive.
